            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Chronicles.12:19-14:17",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Chronicles%2012%3A19-14%3A17%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3ESome%20men%20from%20Manasseh%20defected%20from%20the%20Israelite%20army%20and%20joined%20David%20when%20he%20set%20out%20with%20the%20Philistines%20to%20fight%20against%20Saul.%20But%20as%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20the%20Philistine%20rulers%20refused%20to%20let%20David%20and%20his%20men%20go%20with%20them.%20After%20much%20discussion%2C%20they%20sent%20them%20back%2C%20for%20they%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIt%20will%20cost%20us%20our%20heads%20if%20David%20switches%20loyalties%20to%20Saul%20and%20turns%20against%20us.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_20%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EHere%20is%20a%20list%20of%20the%20men%20from%20Manasseh%20who%20defected%20to%20David%20as%20he%20was%20returning%20to%20Ziklag%3A%20Adnah%2C%20Jozabad%2C%20Jediael%2C%20Michael%2C%20Jozabad%2C%20Elihu%2C%20and%20Zillethai.%20Each%20commanded%201%2C000%20troops%20from%20the%20tribe%20of%20Manasseh.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_21%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20helped%20David%20chase%20down%20bands%20of%20raiders%2C%20for%20they%20were%20all%20brave%20and%20able%20warriors%20who%20became%20commanders%20in%20his%20army.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_22%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EDay%20after%20day%20more%20men%20joined%20David%20until%20he%20had%20a%20great%20army%2C%20like%20the%20army%20of%20God.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_23%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20are%20the%20numbers%20of%20armed%20warriors%20who%20joined%20David%20at%20Hebron.%20They%20were%20all%20eager%20to%20see%20David%20become%20king%20instead%20of%20Saul%2C%20just%20as%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20promised.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_24%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20tribe%20of%20Judah%2C%20there%20were%206%2C800%20warriors%20armed%20with%20shields%20and%20spears.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_25%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20tribe%20of%20Simeon%2C%20there%20were%207%2C100%20brave%20warriors.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_26%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20tribe%20of%20Levi%2C%20there%20were%204%2C600%20warriors.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_27%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20included%20Jehoiada%2C%20leader%20of%20the%20family%20of%20Aaron%2C%20who%20had%203%2C700%20under%20his%20command.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_28%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20also%20included%20Zadok%2C%20a%20brave%20young%20warrior%2C%20with%2022%26%23xA0%3Bmembers%20of%20his%20family%20who%20were%20all%20officers.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_29%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20tribe%20of%20Benjamin%2C%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20relatives%2C%20there%20were%203%2C000%20warriors.%20Most%20of%20the%20men%20from%20Benjamin%20had%20remained%20loyal%20to%20Saul%20until%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_30%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2230%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20tribe%20of%20Ephraim%2C%20there%20were%2020%2C800%20brave%20warriors%2C%20each%20highly%20respected%20in%20his%20own%20clan.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_31%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2231%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E31%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20half-tribe%20of%20Manasseh%20west%20of%20the%20Jordan%2C%2018%2C000%20men%20were%20designated%20by%20name%20to%20help%20David%20become%20king.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_32%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2232%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20tribe%20of%20Issachar%2C%20there%20were%20200%26%23xA0%3Bleaders%20of%20the%20tribe%20with%20their%20relatives.%20All%20these%20men%20understood%20the%20signs%20of%20the%20times%20and%20knew%20the%20best%20course%20for%20Israel%20to%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_33%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2233%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E33%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20tribe%20of%20Zebulun%2C%20there%20were%2050%2C000%20skilled%20warriors.%20They%20were%20fully%20armed%20and%20prepared%20for%20battle%20and%20completely%20loyal%20to%20David.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_34%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2234%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E34%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20tribe%20of%20Naphtali%2C%20there%20were%201%2C000%20officers%20and%2037%2C000%20warriors%20armed%20with%20shields%20and%20spears.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_35%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2235%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E35%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20tribe%20of%20Dan%2C%20there%20were%2028%2C600%20warriors%2C%20all%20prepared%20for%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_36%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2236%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E36%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20tribe%20of%20Asher%2C%20there%20were%2040%2C000%20trained%20warriors%2C%20all%20prepared%20for%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_37%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2237%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E37%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20east%20side%20of%20the%20Jordan%20River%26%23x2014%3Bwhere%20the%20tribes%20of%20Reuben%20and%20Gad%20and%20the%20half-tribe%20of%20Manasseh%20lived%26%23x2014%3Bthere%20were%20120%2C000%20troops%20armed%20with%20every%20kind%20of%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_38%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2238%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E38%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20these%20men%20came%20in%20battle%20array%20to%20Hebron%20with%20the%20single%20purpose%20of%20making%20David%20the%20king%20over%20all%20Israel.%20In%20fact%2C%20everyone%20in%20Israel%20agreed%20that%20David%20should%20be%20their%20king.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_39%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2239%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E39%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20feasted%20and%20drank%20with%20David%20for%20three%20days%2C%20for%20preparations%20had%20been%20made%20by%20their%20relatives%20for%20their%20arrival.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_12_40%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2240%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E40%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20people%20from%20as%20far%20away%20as%20Issachar%2C%20Zebulun%2C%20and%20Naphtali%20brought%20food%20on%20donkeys%2C%20camels%2C%20mules%2C%20and%20oxen.%20Vast%20supplies%20of%20flour%2C%20fig%20cakes%2C%20clusters%20of%20raisins%2C%20wine%2C%20olive%20oil%2C%20cattle%2C%20sheep%2C%20and%20goats%20were%20brought%20to%20the%20celebration.%20There%20was%20great%20joy%20throughout%20the%20land%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20Attempts%20to%20Move%20the%20Ark%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20consulted%20with%20all%20his%20officials%2C%20including%20the%20generals%20and%20captains%20of%20his%20army.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20commanders%20of%20thousands%20and%20of%20hundreds.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20addressed%20the%20entire%20assembly%20of%20Israel%20as%20follows%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BIf%20you%20approve%20and%20if%20it%20is%20the%20will%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20our%20God%2C%20let%20us%20send%20messages%20to%20all%20the%20Israelites%20throughout%20the%20land%2C%20including%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites%20in%20their%20towns%20and%20pasturelands.%20Let%20us%20invite%20them%20to%20come%20and%20join%20us.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20is%20time%20to%20bring%20back%20the%20Ark%20of%20our%20God%2C%20for%20we%20neglected%20it%20during%20the%20reign%20of%20Saul.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20whole%20assembly%20agreed%20to%20this%2C%20for%20the%20people%20could%20see%20it%20was%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20David%20summoned%20all%20Israel%2C%20from%20the%20Shihor%20Brook%20of%20Egypt%20in%20the%20south%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20town%20of%20Lebo-hamath%20in%20the%20north%2C%20to%20join%20in%20bringing%20the%20Ark%20of%20God%20from%20Kiriath-jearim.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20David%20and%20all%20Israel%20went%20to%20Baalah%20of%20Judah%20(also%20called%20Kiriath-jearim)%20to%20bring%20back%20the%20Ark%20of%20God%2C%20which%20bears%20the%20name%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20Ark%20of%20God%2C%20where%20the%20Name%20is%20proclaimed%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20name.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20who%20is%20enthroned%20between%20the%20cherubim.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20placed%20the%20Ark%20of%20God%20on%20a%20new%20cart%20and%20brought%20it%20from%20Abinadab%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house.%20Uzzah%20and%20Ahio%20were%20guiding%20the%20cart.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20and%20all%20Israel%20were%20celebrating%20before%20God%20with%20all%20their%20might%2C%20singing%20songs%20and%20playing%20all%20kinds%20of%20musical%20instruments%26%23x2014%3Blyres%2C%20harps%2C%20tambourines%2C%20cymbals%2C%20and%20trumpets.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20when%20they%20arrived%20at%20the%20threshing%20floor%20of%20Nacon%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20parallel%20text%20at%202%26%23xA0%3BSam%206%3A6%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EKidon.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20oxen%20stumbled%2C%20and%20Uzzah%20reached%20out%20his%20hand%20to%20steady%20the%20Ark.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20anger%20was%20aroused%20against%20Uzzah%2C%20and%20he%20struck%20him%20dead%20because%20he%20had%20laid%20his%20hand%20on%20the%20Ark.%20So%20Uzzah%20died%20there%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20God.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20was%20angry%20because%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20anger%20had%20burst%20out%20against%20Uzzah.%20He%20named%20that%20place%20Perez-uzzah%20(which%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Bto%20burst%20out%20against%20Uzzah%26%23x201D%3B)%2C%20as%20it%20is%20still%20called%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20was%20now%20afraid%20of%20God%2C%20and%20he%20asked%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BHow%20can%20I%20ever%20bring%20the%20Ark%20of%20God%20back%20into%20my%20care%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20David%20did%20not%20move%20the%20Ark%20into%20the%20City%20of%20David.%20Instead%2C%20he%20took%20it%20to%20the%20house%20of%20Obed-edom%20of%20Gath.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_13_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Ark%20of%20God%20remained%20there%20in%20Obed-edom%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house%20for%20three%20months%2C%20and%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20blessed%20the%20household%20of%20Obed-edom%20and%20everything%20he%20owned.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_14_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Palace%20and%20Family%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20King%20Hiram%20of%20Tyre%20sent%20messengers%20to%20David%2C%20along%20with%20cedar%20timber%2C%20and%20stonemasons%20and%20carpenters%20to%20build%20him%20a%20palace.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_14_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20David%20realized%20that%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20confirmed%20him%20as%20king%20over%20Israel%20and%20had%20greatly%20blessed%20his%20kingdom%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20his%20people%20Israel.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_14_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20David%20married%20more%20wives%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20and%20they%20had%20more%20sons%20and%20daughters.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_14_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20are%20the%20names%20of%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sons%20who%20were%20born%20in%20Jerusalem%3A%20Shammua%2C%20Shobab%2C%20Nathan%2C%20Solomon%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_14_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EIbhar%2C%20Elishua%2C%20Elpelet%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_14_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3ENogah%2C%20Nepheg%2C%20Japhia%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_14_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EElishama%2C%20Eliada%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E14%3A7%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EBeeliada%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Eliada%3B%20compare%203%3A8%20and%20parallel%20text%20at%202%26%23xA0%3BSam%205%3A16.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20Eliphelet.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20ori